  "text": "Object handling motions-pregrasping, squeezing, and releasing-are defined with the help of a contact stance planner as in [CITATION_1] . Since this planner guarantees feasibility only at specific postures, we have to verify, through simulations, that the interpolated motions are also feasible. For example, the second scenario from below in Fig. 1 turned out to be unfeasible on our humanoid, because of the body grasp configuration.",
